{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Information technology grows in an exponential manner."},{"time":4000,"text":"It's not linear. And our intuition is linear."},{"time":8000,"text":"When we walked through the savanna a thousand years ago"},{"time":10000,"text":"we made linear predictions where that animal would be,"},{"time":12000,"text":"and that worked fine. It's hardwired in our brains."},{"time":15000,"text":"But the pace of exponential growth"},{"time":18000,"text":"is really what describes information technologies."},{"time":21000,"text":"And it's not just computation."},{"time":24000,"text":"There is a big difference between linear and exponential growth."},{"time":26000,"text":"If I take 30 steps linearly -- one, two, three, four, five --"},{"time":30000,"text":"I get to 30."},{"time":32000,"text":"If I take 30 steps exponentially -- two, four, eight, 16 --"},{"time":35000,"text":"I get to a billion."},{"time":37000,"text":"It makes a huge difference."},{"time":39000,"text":"And that really describes information technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41000,"text":"When I was a student at MIT,"},{"time":43000,"text":"we all shared one computer that took up a whole building."},{"time":45000,"text":"The computer in your cellphone today is a million times cheaper,"},{"time":48000,"text":"a million times smaller,"},{"time":50000,"text":"a thousand times more powerful."},{"time":52000,"text":"That's a billion-fold increase in capability per dollar"},{"time":55000,"text":"that we've actually experienced since I was a student."},{"time":57000,"text":"And we're going to do it again in the next 25 years."},{"time":60000,"text":"Information technology progresses"},{"time":62000,"text":"through a series of S-curves"},{"time":64000,"text":"where each one is a different paradigm."},{"time":66000,"text":"So people say, \"What's going to happen when Moore's Law comes to an end?\""},{"time":69000,"text":"Which will happen around 2020."},{"time":71000,"text":"We'll then go to the next paradigm."},{"time":73000,"text":"And Moore's Law was not the first paradigm"},{"time":75000,"text":"to bring exponential growth to computing."},{"time":77000,"text":"The exponential growth of computing started"},{"time":79000,"text":"decades before Gordon Moore was even born."},{"time":81000,"text":"And it doesn't just apply to computation."},{"time":85000,"text":"It's really any technology where we can measure"},{"time":87000,"text":"the underlying information properties."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90000,"text":"Here we have 49 famous computers. I put them in a logarithmic graph."},{"time":94000,"text":"The logarithmic scale hides the scale of the increase,"},{"time":98000,"text":"because this represents trillions-fold increase"},{"time":100000,"text":"since the 1890 census."},{"time":103000,"text":"In 1950s they were shrinking vacuum tubes,"},{"time":105000,"text":"making them smaller and smaller. They finally hit a wall;"},{"time":108000,"text":"they couldn't shrink the vacuum tube any more and keep the vacuum."},{"time":110000,"text":"And that was the end of the shrinking of vacuum tubes,"},{"time":113000,"text":"but it was not the end of the exponential growth of computing."},{"time":116000,"text":"We went to the fourth paradigm, transistors,"},{"time":118000,"text":"and finally integrated circuits."},{"time":120000,"text":"When that comes to an end we'll go to the sixth paradigm;"},{"time":122000,"text":"three-dimensional self-organizing molecular circuits."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126000,"text":"But what's even more amazing, really, than this"},{"time":129000,"text":"fantastic scale of progress,"},{"time":131000,"text":"is that -- look at how predictable this is."},{"time":133000,"text":"I mean this went through thick and thin,"},{"time":135000,"text":"through war and peace, through boom times and recessions."},{"time":138000,"text":"The Great Depression made not a dent in this exponential progression."},{"time":142000,"text":"We'll see the same thing in the economic recession we're having now."},{"time":146000,"text":"At least the exponential growth of information technology capability"},{"time":149000,"text":"will continue unabated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152000,"text":"And I just updated these graphs."},{"time":154000,"text":"Because I had them through 2002 in my book, \"The Singularity is Near.\""},{"time":157000,"text":"So we updated them,"},{"time":159000,"text":"so I could present it here, to 2007."},{"time":162000,"text":"And I was asked, \"Well aren't you nervous?"},{"time":164000,"text":"Maybe it kind of didn't stay on this exponential progression.\""},{"time":168000,"text":"I was a little nervous"},{"time":170000,"text":"because maybe the data wouldn't be right,"},{"time":172000,"text":"but I've done this now for 30 years,"},{"time":174000,"text":"and it has stayed on this exponential progression."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177000,"text":"Look at this graph here.You could buy one transistor for a dollar in 1968."},{"time":180000,"text":"You can buy half a billion today,"},{"time":182000,"text":"and they are actually better, because they are faster."},{"time":184000,"text":"But look at how predictable this is."},{"time":186000,"text":"And I'd say this knowledge is over-fitting to past data."},{"time":189000,"text":"I've been making these forward-looking predictions for about 30 years."},{"time":193000,"text":"And the cost of a transistor cycle,"},{"time":195000,"text":"which is a measure of the price performance of electronics,"},{"time":197000,"text":"comes down about every year."},{"time":199000,"text":"That's a 50 percent deflation rate."},{"time":201000,"text":"And it's also true of other examples,"},{"time":203000,"text":"like DNA data or brain data."},{"time":205000,"text":"But we more than make up for that."},{"time":207000,"text":"We actually ship more than twice as much"},{"time":209000,"text":"of every form of information technology."},{"time":211000,"text":"We've had 18 percent growth in constant dollars"},{"time":214000,"text":"in every form of information technology for the last half-century,"},{"time":217000,"text":"despite the fact that you can get twice as much of it each year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221000,"text":"This is a completely different example."},{"time":223000,"text":"This is not Moore's Law."},{"time":225000,"text":"The amount of DNA data"},{"time":227000,"text":"we've sequenced has doubled every year."},{"time":229000,"text":"The cost has come down by half every year."},{"time":232000,"text":"And this has been a smooth progression"},{"time":234000,"text":"since the beginning of the genome project."},{"time":236000,"text":"And halfway through the project, skeptics said,"},{"time":238000,"text":"\"Well, this is not working out. You're halfway through the genome project"},{"time":241000,"text":"and you've finished one percent of the project.\""},{"time":243000,"text":"But that was really right on schedule."},{"time":245000,"text":"Because if you double one percent seven more times,"},{"time":247000,"text":"which is exactly what happened,"},{"time":249000,"text":"you get 100 percent. And the project was finished on time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252000,"text":"Communication technologies:"},{"time":254000,"text":"50 different ways to measure this,"},{"time":256000,"text":"the number of bits being moved around, the size of the Internet."},{"time":259000,"text":"But this has progressed at an exponential pace."},{"time":261000,"text":"This is deeply democratizing."},{"time":263000,"text":"I wrote, over 20 years ago in \"The Age of Intelligent Machines,\""},{"time":266000,"text":"when the Soviet Union was going strong, that it would be swept away"},{"time":269000,"text":"by this growth of decentralized communication."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273000,"text":"And we will have plenty of computation as we go through the 21st century"},{"time":276000,"text":"to do things like simulate regions of the human brain."},{"time":280000,"text":"But where will we get the software?"},{"time":282000,"text":"Some critics say, \"Oh, well software is stuck in the mud.\""},{"time":285000,"text":"But we are learning more and more about the human brain."},{"time":287000,"text":"Spatial resolution of brain scanning is doubling every year."},{"time":290000,"text":"The amount of data we're getting about the brain is doubling every year."},{"time":293000,"text":"And we're showing that we can actually turn this data"},{"time":296000,"text":"into working models and simulations of brain regions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299000,"text":"There is about 20 regions of the brain that have been modeled,"},{"time":301000,"text":"simulated and tested:"},{"time":303000,"text":"the auditory cortex, regions of the visual cortex;"},{"time":306000,"text":"cerebellum, where we do our skill formation;"},{"time":308000,"text":"slices of the cerebral cortex, where we do our rational thinking."},{"time":312000,"text":"And all of this has fueled"},{"time":314000,"text":"an increase, very smooth and predictable, of productivity."},{"time":317000,"text":"We've gone from 30 dollars to 130 dollars"},{"time":319000,"text":"in constant dollars in the value of an average hour of human labor,"},{"time":323000,"text":"fueled by this information technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326000,"text":"And we're all concerned about energy and the environment."},{"time":329000,"text":"Well this is a logarithmic graph."},{"time":331000,"text":"This represents a smooth doubling,"},{"time":333000,"text":"every two years, of the amount of solar energy we're creating,"},{"time":337000,"text":"particularly as we're now applying nanotechnology,"},{"time":339000,"text":"a form of information technology, to solar panels."},{"time":342000,"text":"And we're only eight doublings away"},{"time":344000,"text":"from it meeting 100 percent of our energy needs."},{"time":346000,"text":"And there is 10 thousand times more sunlight than we need."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350000,"text":"We ultimately will merge with this technology. It's already very close to us."},{"time":355000,"text":"When I was a student it was across campus, now it's in our pockets."},{"time":358000,"text":"What used to take up a building now fits in our pockets."},{"time":361000,"text":"What now fits in our pockets would fit in a blood cell in 25 years."},{"time":364000,"text":"And we will begin to actually deeply influence"},{"time":368000,"text":"our health and our intelligence,"},{"time":370000,"text":"as we get closer and closer to this technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374000,"text":"Based on that we are announcing, here at TED,"},{"time":377000,"text":"in true TED tradition, Singularity University."},{"time":380000,"text":"It's a new university"},{"time":382000,"text":"that's founded by Peter Diamandis, who is here in the audience,"},{"time":384000,"text":"and myself."},{"time":386000,"text":"It's backed by NASA and Google,"},{"time":388000,"text":"and other leaders in the high-tech and science community."},{"time":392000,"text":"And our goal was to assemble the leaders,"},{"time":395000,"text":"both teachers and students,"},{"time":397000,"text":"in these exponentially growing information technologies,"},{"time":399000,"text":"and their application."},{"time":401000,"text":"But Larry Page made an impassioned speech"},{"time":403000,"text":"at our organizing meeting,"},{"time":405000,"text":"saying we should devote this study"},{"time":410000,"text":"to actually addressing some of the major challenges facing humanity."},{"time":414000,"text":"And if we did that, then Google would back this."},{"time":416000,"text":"And so that's what we've done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418000,"text":"The last third of the nine-week intensive summer session"},{"time":422000,"text":"will be devoted to a group project to address"},{"time":424000,"text":"some major challenge of humanity."},{"time":426000,"text":"Like for example, applying the Internet,"},{"time":428000,"text":"which is now ubiquitous, in the rural areas of China or in Africa,"},{"time":433000,"text":"to bringing health information"},{"time":435000,"text":"to developing areas of the world."},{"time":438000,"text":"And these projects will continue past these sessions,"},{"time":441000,"text":"using collaborative interactive communication."},{"time":444000,"text":"All the intellectual property that is created and taught"},{"time":448000,"text":"will be online and available,"},{"time":450000,"text":"and developed online in a collaborative fashion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453000,"text":"Here is our founding meeting."},{"time":455000,"text":"But this is being announced today."},{"time":457000,"text":"It will be permanently headquartered in Silicon Valley,"},{"time":460000,"text":"at the NASA Ames research center."},{"time":462000,"text":"There are different programs for graduate students,"},{"time":464000,"text":"for executives at different companies."},{"time":467000,"text":"The first six tracks here -- artificial intelligence,"},{"time":469000,"text":"advanced computing technologies, biotechnology, nanotechnology --"},{"time":472000,"text":"are the different core areas of information technology."},{"time":476000,"text":"Then we are going to apply them to the other areas,"},{"time":478000,"text":"like energy, ecology,"},{"time":481000,"text":"policy law and ethics, entrepreneurship,"},{"time":483000,"text":"so that people can bring these new technologies to the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487000,"text":"So we're very appreciative of the support we've gotten"},{"time":492000,"text":"from both the intellectual leaders, the high-tech leaders,"},{"time":494000,"text":"particularly Google and NASA."},{"time":496000,"text":"This is an exciting new venture."},{"time":498000,"text":"And we invite you to participate. Thank you very much."},{"time":501000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}